He is wearing a shirt with the clubâ€™s emblem, on which it says â€œ20 years.â€

(The Red Front).

And in the third image it says: â€œAnd we love the red.â€

The fourth and final image â€“ another choreography from the same match.
A design that mimics an ancient Greek-Roman wall painting, with mythological scenes.

At the center of the choreography is the clubâ€™s emblem,

The authorities of Leeuwarden (SC Cambuur) Rotterdam (Feyenoord) and Utrecht (FC Utrecht) will be allowed to use a new, portable device, the so-called Mini-ID, at home games of their clubs. The device, which fans are required to wear, allows the police to check in real time whether someone is near the stadium. Anyone who comes near despite an area ban will be immediately visible.
